# Member Roles Settings and Grouping

## Goal Description
Implement a dynamic system to assign roles (Tester, FE dev, BE dev, Team Leader) to team members, group/sort the daily meeting view by these roles, and use this role data to populate the "Blocked by" dropdowns instead of hardcoded lists. Per request, this must NOT modify `db.json`, so a new `roles.json` data store will be introduced.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration / API Layer
#### [NEW] `src/app/api/roles/route.ts`
Create a new API route similar to [api/data/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/api/data/route.ts) that safely reads/writes to `data/roles.json`. It will map `Person Name` -> `Role`.

#### [NEW] `src/lib/hooks/useRoles.ts`
Create a React hook providing `roles` state, `updateRole(person, role)`, and `isLoading` context using `SWR` or just native `fetch` polling to the `/api/roles` endpoint.

---

### UI / View Layer
#### [MODIFY] `src/app/page.tsx`
- Integrate `useRoles` to fetch the member-role mapping.
- Pass `roles` to [DailyMeetingView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#2477-2870) and [StandupInspector](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx#46-444).

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx)
- **Role Ordering**: Modify the sorting logic of `allPersonData` so it groups people by their roles: 
  1. Tester
  2. BE dev
  3. FE dev
  4. Team Leader
  5. Unassigned/Other
- **Settings UI**: Add a small "Member Roles" settings button (e.g. next to the team filters) that opens a `Dialog` or `Popover` listing all known team members with a `<select>` to assign them a Role.

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx)
- Replace the hardcoded `TEAM_LEADERS` array in the "Blocked By" dropdown.
- Render `<optgroup>`s dynamically based on the fetched `roles` dictionary. If a person is assigned "Tester", append them under the "Tester" `<optgroup>`, etc.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A - Sprint Relay has no automated tests setup around this feature, but `npm run build` will verify type enforcement.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the UI, click "Member Roles" settings, and assign a few members distinct roles (Tester, FE, BE...).
2. Observe that `data/roles.json` is successfully created and updated in the project root folder without modifying `db.json`.
3. Verify that the Daily Meeting View automatically reorders [PersonSingleView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#766-1112) cards based on the sorted Role hierarchy.
4. Click on a task to open [StandupInspector](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx#46-444), toggle "Is this task stalled?", and verify the "Blocked By" dropdown dynamically reflects the assigned groups.
